19/10/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- NATO Secretary-General Anders Fogh Rasmussen said on Saturday (October 17th) in an interview with the Belgrade-based daily Vecernje Novosti that the security situation in the Western Balkans is stable and that European prospects for the region are becoming tangible. 
According to him, Euro-Atlantic integration is the best guarantee for long-term stability in the Balkans. 
He pointed out that NATO wants to develop its partnership with Serbia, adding it is important that Belgrade continues to implement a constructive policy towards Kosovo. 
(Beta, Tanjug, Medjunarodni Radio Srbija - 18/10/09; Vecernje Novosti - 17/10/09)
